      "role": "user",
      "content": "valgrind isn't really a great option for our specific hardware setup because of the overhead and the kernel constraints. i need something a bit more lightweight for the actual target. are there specific patterns or common coding mistakes in embedded c++ that usually cause these kinds of slow, incremental leaks? like, besides just a missing delete, what should i specifically be looking for in the code?",
